reviewText: Thanks to WWE 24/7, I relived an old PPV from the In Your House PPV series in 1996 subtitled "Mind Games."  Now for those who don't remember the original In Your House PPV series, they were only 2 hours long at a cheap price (less than $20) and were the filler events inbetween WWE's (then WWF) big PPV's like Royal Rumble, WrestleMania, King Of The Ring, SummerSlam, and Survivor Series.  During this time, Shawn Michaels was a fighing WWF Champion and had a new challenger in Mankind, who recently revealed his alliance with Paul Bearer.  Eventhough this PPV was remembered for various moments like the main event along with a few inring debuts for wrestlers still around today, this show is mostly remembered for what happened with a certain set of EXTREME people sitting in the front row.Strap Match: Savio Vega vs. Justin "Hawk" Bradshaw - Before we knew him as a member of the A.P.A. and even a blackjack, J.B.L.'s first character was Justin "Hawk" Bradshaw & this was his PPV debut.  Savio was a little winded from wrestling only minutes earlier on the pre-game show.  This match wasn't as good as the strap match Savio had with Austin months earlier since it was short & really just a backdrop for what happened at ringside earlier in the match...when Extreme Championship Wrestling stars Tommy Dreamer, Paul Heyman, and Sandman caused a disturbance when Sandman spat beer in Savio's face leading to all the backstage agents coming out & escourting them out the building.[The ECW incident can be seen on "The Rise & Fall Of ECW" DVD]Jose Lothario vs. Jim Cornette - This was a battle of the managers & nothing more past a 1 min. comedic match.Tag Team Champions Smokin' Gunns vs. Owen Hart & British Bulldog - This was an unusual setup as both teams were heels at this time with various interesting things happening before the match got started.  Backstage Jim Cornette's lawyer Clarence Mason tricked Jim into signing over the contracts of Owen & Bulldog to Mason, Owen & Bulldog ruined Sunny's giant poster of herself, and you clearly saw problems between Billy & Bart in over Sunny.  Owen & Bulldog dominated most of the match by working over Bart's leg & even gaining the crowd support in the process before another miscommunication between Billy & Bart due to Billy being attention to Sunny instead of the match cost them the Tag Team Titles along with Sunny herself who fired them afterwards.Mark Henry vs. Jerry Lawler - Earlier in the night, it was the future J.B.L.'s PPV debut but in this case, it's Mark Henry's WWF inring debut.  Lawler was nothing more than just a body for Henry to dominate & heavily sell his limited offense which worked as Lawler made Henry look better than he really was at that time.  Look out for the cameo appearences from Marty Jannettty, Leif Cassidy (Al Snow), and Hunter Hearst Helmsley afterwards.Final Curtain Match: Undertaker vs. Goldust - This was the final match in their 3 match series over the previous In Your House events with the rules for this match being that it can only end in a pinfall.  Just like their previous match at Beware Of Dog (didn't see the one at International Incident two months later/earlier), this was a solid encounter with both men going back & forth with each other before Undertaker in the end finally chokeslammed & tombstoned his way to a victory over Goldust.WWF Champion Shawn Michaels vs. Mankind - Mick Foley wrote in his "Have A Nice Day" book that this was the best match of his career & was concidered by WWE as the best match of 1996. With HBK's high flyin' lucha libre influenced style mixed with Mankind's hardcore daredevil style made for one hell of a match with so many intense moments, you have to see this one to believe everything they went through with the cameos of people like Sysco Sid, Vader, and Undertaker towards the end only adding to the enviroment instead of taking away from it.[Also available on "Shawn Michaels: From The Vault", "Mick Foley: Hard Knocks & Cheap Pops", "Mick Foley's Greatest Hits & Misses" DVD sets]In the end, this event was typical of the In Your House PPV's they had back then where you would have a couple of average to good 3 star matches on the card with one match (usually the main event) sticking out above all the others.  The standout performances here were the tag team title match, solid encounter with Taker & Goldust along with the main event that was proclaimed as the match of the year by WWF along with Foley's favorite wrestling performance.  This is an In Your House PPV I would recommend at a reasonable cheap price if you were a fan of the WWF product around this time.

reviewText: Once again I review an old schoold rasslin Pay Per View. WWF In Your House Mind Games. I'm going to tell the backstory leading into some of the matches. On The August 19th episode of RAW Mankind got a shot at The WWF Championship. Meanwhile Shawn Michaels took on Yokozuna & Jim Cornette came down to ringside & attacked Jose Lathero. On The September 9th episode of RAW Jose Lathero challenged Jim Cornette at Mind Games. The following week Jim Cornette had a public workout which was funny. Getting back to the title match Mankind cut a really good promo on The September 16th episode of RAW. On a special Friday Night RAW on September 6th Brian Pillman said that at Mind Games. On The September 9th episode of RAW Brian Pillman said that Bret & Owen have reunited. The following week Bret Hart responded by saying that Piillman is a lier. On The August 19th episode of RAW The Druids brought Undertaker's body out & he rose up. On The September 16th episode of RAW that Goldust is on his list of people to go after before he goes after Mankind. On The August 19th episode of RAW The British Bulldog & Owen Hart faced each other in The Intercontenintal title tournament. Bulldog was counted out Sunny who was doing commentary threw soda into his face she also mentioned managing Owen & Bulldog which brought out Jim Cornette & he yelled at her. On The September 16th episode of RAW Owen Hart & The British Bulldog got a shot at The WWF Tag Team Championship at Mind Games. On The Friday Night RAW Jerry Lawler held a King's Court his guest was Mark Henry basically King put him down to set up a match at Mind Games. That is the backstory heading into this event the buyrate was a 0.48 that is down from The Triple Header which got a 0.70.The current WWF Champions at the time wereWWF Champion Shawn Michaels March 31st 1996WWF Intercontenintal Champion June 23rd vacated August 12th 1996WWF Tag Team Championship The Smoking Gunns Billy & Bart May 26th 1996Date September 22, 1996Attendance 15,000Venue CoreStates CenterCity Philadelphia, PennsylvaniaFree For AllJerry Lawler & Mark Henry had a debate Lawler called Mark Henry an amature. Lawler said that Mark Henry might lose control of his bodily functions tonight. Mark Henry said that he will let his actions do the talking for him. Lawler smacked Mark Henry.Then they show the kind of schedule Shawn Michaels has been on for the past 6 months.Savio Vega Def Marty Janetty with Leif Cassidy * & quarter of a starfrom the back Justin Hawk Bradshaw cuts a promo where he is mad that he hasn't been on a Pay Per View yet. There were ECW chants going during the match Vince said if you hear a unusal sound there is local wrestling franchise in attendance so to speak. Ross said atleast they bought tickets. Bradshaw attacked Savio Vega with a bullrope after the match. Savio Vega challenged Bradshaw to a strap match for later on.Todd Pettengill interviewed Sunny who was confronted by Jim Cornette.They show a video package for The Final Curtain Match with Undertaker & Goldust.Jim Ross interviewed Mankind & Paul Bearer. Mankind said he will destroy Shawn Michaels & win The WWF title. Cause if he wins The WWF title he will never have to go back to that Bingo Hall again. He said Have A Nice Day.Then you get to The Pay Per View the opening is decent.Caribbean Strap MatchSavio Vega Def Justin Hawk Bradshaw with Uncle Zebikah *The Sandman spit beer in Savio's face which was funny. This was a p  i  s  s poor match it's just that I'm not a fan of strap matches I really only liked the 1 with Vader & Sting & the 1 with Austin & Savio.A video package for Jim Cornette vs Jose Lathero was shown.Jose Lathero Def Jim Cornette DUDThey showed showed Fake Razor & Diesel attack Savio in the back. It was weird seeing Jose Lather come out to Shawn Michaels music.Brian Pillman came out & cut a promo on Philadelphia which was entertaining. He had Owen Hart come out he said that Bret promised him that he would be here. He said that Bret is scared of Stone Cold Steve Austin who had been challenging him recently. Austin said when you put the letter s in front of Hit Man that is my opinion of Bret Hart.WWF Tag Team ChampionshipOwen Hart & The British Bulldog with Clerance Mason Def Champions The Smoking Gunns Billy & Bart with Sunny ** & half starsA decent match definitly 1 of The Gunns better matches Sunny turned on The Gunns after the matchKevin Kelly interviewed Paul Bearer & Mankind. Paul Bearer said that it is The Creatures Of The Night fault that I did what I did. Mankind said that it is his destiny to destroy Shawn Michaels & cuddle that heavyweight title. Then we will all Hve A Nice Day.Mark Henry Def Jerry "The King" Lawler half a star & that is being nice.The New Rockers & Hunter Hearst Helmsley all came out & were pwnd by Mark Henry.They show where there will be an Unsanctioned Buried Alive Match at the next In Your House.Final Curtain MatchThe Undertaker Def Goldust with Marlena *Other than there Casket Match at Beware Of Dog I didn't care for Undertaker & Goldust's matchesKevin Kelly interviewed Shawn Michaels he said that he is going to think on the job.WWF ChampionshipChampion Shawn Michaels with Jose Lathero Def Mankind with Paul Bearer by disqualification **** & 3 quarters of a starSome Druids brought a Casket out that Mankind came out of. Vader caused the disqualification when he attacked Michaels Sycho Sid came out & him & Vader started brawling. Mankind put The Mandible Claw on Shawn Michaels he was going to put him in The Casket but Undertaker was in it & he chased after Mankind & Paul Bearer. This match was a brawl but it was great & the best thing on this Pay Per View the only 2 matches worth a d  a  m  n were The Tag title match which was decent & the WWF title match. The rest you have 2 1 star matches a DUD & half of a star match & there is a seller on here asking $500 for this show if you feel you need to see it go get a bootleg or see in the internet. A nothing card in a point in time where Vince was trying to get his ducks in row.
